AGI - "I don't know if anyone from the Pd thinks of a possible congress. I think it would not be understood neither by our members nor by our voters. Also because&nbsp; it would take months to discuss". This is what the MEP and President of the Pd, Stefano Bonaccini says, says, "The air that draws", on La7.
"No one asks for the resignation of the secretary, on which we trust and to whom I believe, I first. We really helped in these two years," adds Bonaccini: "We have the administrative and six regional elections in autumn which votes a third of the Italians. I would take care of that because &nbsp; it will be a political vote". &nbsp;
Bonaccini then dwelt on what happened after the 'strap' of the Pd delegation in Brussels on the ReArm and on that "key" asked loudly from the internal minority, but "necessary" also for the secretary Schlein. That clarification, underlines the president of the Pd, "was with the vote in the Chamber and the Senate, with the compact vote of the parliamentary groups on the resolution of the Pd.
"There was a difference in opinion on the vote of abstention," recalls Bonaccini, but "the Chamber and the Senate" the PD was "compact and united". Now, for Bonaccini, we need to put together a field capable of winning the next political elections.
"Certainly in the territories we are ready" and "we have shown that the centerleft can be together", but we must "work to highlight the things that unite and not those that divide.> There is someone in my party who says 'divisi si vince', I think exactly the opposite because it is enough to be memori of October 2022>: the right all united with 40% of the real votes had the two-thirds of the elected in Parliament because the electoral law rewards those who join >, the center left each for themselves and nobody with the others, divided in three parts we have taken a beautiful batosta>. I hope that all those who call themselves alternatives to the right and Meloni, if they do not want to keep it to the government for the next thirty years, find the reasons for an alternative because today this is certainly not a more just and competitive country than Meloni had found it before the elections," he concludes.&nbsp;
